avpkg commands (updated, changes not yet implemented):

avpkg -h, avpkg --help ::: Show options
---
avpkg -v, avpkg --version ::: Show version info
---
avpkg -e ::: Edit repos
---
avpkg -l ::: Lists installed packages
---
avpkg -i uses:
-i ::: Shows system info
-i <pkg> ::: Shows info about system or package(s)
---
avpkg -a uses:
-a <pkg> ::: Installs package(s)
-a <pkg> -v <ver> ::: Installs specified version of package(s)
-a -s <pkg> ::: Only available as administrator | Installs package(s) for the logged in administrator and users managed by current administrator
---
avpkg -t /<filepath>/<pkg.tar> ::: Installs tar package(s)
---
avpkg -r uses:
-r ::: Removes unnecessary packages and dependencies
-r <pkg> ::: Removes package(s)
-r <pkg> -v <ver> ::: Removes specified version of package(s) if multiple versions of the same package are installed on the system
---
avpkg -u uses:
-u ::: Updates system and packages
-u <pkg> ::: Updates specified package(s)
-u -m ::: Applies major system upgrades (Windfall v1 -> Windfall v2)
---
avpkg -d uses:
-d ::: Downgrades system by 1 major version if possible (Windfall v1 <- Windfall v2)
-d <pkg> ::: Downgrades specified package(s)
---
avpkg dnu ::: Opens do-not-update list editor
---
avpkg -s ::: Searches repos for package(s)
---
avpkg -f ::: Attempts to find and fix issues
